						               													<description>Players are the candidates to be the new &amp;quot;God of Luck&amp;quot;. By rolling dices, players try to complete various tasks to raise his Fu-Chi, which means good fortune. Players also can employ many Chinese traditional immortals to help himself. The player who earns the most Fu-Chi will become the new &amp;quot;God of Luck&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;User Summary:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On each turn, player rolls a specific number of dices, if the result of some dices match the requirement of a hand card, which also calls Fu-Chi card, then the player could play that card from hand into his playing area. Player may discard some Fu-Chi cards from his area to invite an immortal to join him. Pick that immortal character card into his playing area. All of immortals have some special abilities to affect the result of rolling dices, such as seem 2 as 4, or just simply increase the volume of dice pool.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When someone owns 8 immortals, or 2 stacks of Fu-Chi cards have been drawn, the game will enter the final turn after the current turn. In the final turn, player has to do one's best to match the requirement of their hand cards, he cannot invite any immortals in the final turn, but can use the abilities of those invited immortals in the previous turns in his area. After the final turn, any Fu-Chi cards and immortal character cards in one's area would be scored as their illustration. The player with most scores (Fu-Chi) will become the new &amp;quot;God of Luck&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
